data.title: Top things to do in Edmonton
Top things to do in Edmonton, Canada
If you only have a day
data.providerTitle: If you only have a day

placeMetadata.name: TELUS World of Science - Edmonton
placeMetadata.description: Science centre with hands-on exhibits on robots, the human body & more, plus a separate observatory.
placeMetadata.generatedDescription: TELUS World of Science - Edmonton is a top attraction in Northern Alberta, offering interactive science experiences for visitors of all ages. The center features five permanent galleries with hands-on exhibits on topics like robots and the human body, as well as a state-of-the-art IMAX Theatre and a planetarium showcasing captivating shows. Known for hosting major traveling exhibitions such as Harry Potter: The Exhibition and STAR WARS IDENTITIES, this science center also boasts the largest planetarium in Canada.
placeMetadata.address: 11211 142 St NW, Edmonton, AB T5M 4A1, Canada

placeMetadata.name: Edmonton River Float
placeMetadata.address: 9180 Walterdale Hill NW, Edmonton, AB T6E 2V3, Canada

placeMetadata.name: West Edmonton Mall
placeMetadata.description: Among North America's largest malls, this venue includes family attractions & more than 800 shops.
placeMetadata.generatedDescription: West Edmonton Mall, also known as WEM, is one of the largest malls in North America. It features over 800 shops and a wide range of family attractions. Visitors can enjoy activities such as skating, visiting the water park, exploring Galaxyland Amusement Park, experiencing marine life at Sea Life Caverns, playing golf, and more. The mall also houses two hotels: the themed Fantasyland Hotel and the budget-friendly West Edmonton Mall Inn.
placeMetadata.address: 8882 170 St NW, Edmonton, AB T5T 4J2, Canada

placeMetadata.name: Lake Louise Ski Resort & Summer Gondola
placeMetadata.description: Large ski resort with many year-round recreational activities, plus eateries & shops.
placeMetadata.generatedDescription: Located in Banff National Park, the Lake Louise Ski Resort & Summer Gondola is a large year-round recreational destination with numerous activities, dining options, and shops. Nestled in the Canadian Rockies, it offers stunning views and diverse terrain for skiers of all levels. With 139 ski runs and a lift capacity of over 14,000 skiers per hour, it's a popular spot for skiing and snowboarding events.
placeMetadata.address: 1 Whitehorn Rd, Lake Louise, AB T0L 1E0, Canada

placeMetadata.name: Lake Louise
placeMetadata.description: Lake Louise is a hamlet in Banff National Park in the Canadian Rockies, known for its turquoise, glacier-fed lake ringed by high peaks and overlooked by a stately chateau. Hiking trails wind up to the Lake Agnes Tea House for bird's-eye views. There's a canoe dock in summer, and a skating rink on the frozen lake in winter. The Lake Louise Ski Resort features a wildlife interpretive center at the top of a gondola.
placeMetadata.generatedDescription: Nestled in Banff National Park, Lake Louise is a picturesque hamlet renowned for its stunning turquoise lake, encircled by towering peaks and graced by the elegant Fairmont Chateau Lake Louise. Visitors can explore hiking trails leading to the scenic Lake Agnes Tea House or enjoy canoeing in the summer and ice skating during winter on the frozen lake. The nearby Lake Louise Ski Resort offers a wildlife interpretive center at the summit accessible via gondola.
placeMetadata.address: Alberta T0L 1E0, Canada

placeMetadata.name: Moraine Lake
placeMetadata.description: Dramatic, glacier-fed lake with a distinctive blue-green color, plus hiking trails & a canoe dock.
placeMetadata.generatedDescription: Moraine Lake, located about 9 miles outside of Lake Louise village in Banff National Park, is a stunning glacier-fed lake known for its distinctive blue-green color. During the summer, the thaw brings out the vibrant beauty of this natural wonder, attracting visitors to explore its hiking trails and take in the breathtaking scenery. The surrounding peaks offer opportunities for hiking and provide panoramic views of the picturesque lake below.
placeMetadata.address: Improvement District No. 9, AB T0L 1E0, Canada

placeMetadata.name: Jolene's Tea House
placeMetadata.generatedDescription: Nestled in the breathtaking Canadian Rockies, Jolene's Tea House is a charming mountain retreat that invites tea lovers to explore its unique hand-blended varieties. With over 60 flavors to choose from, including delightful options like wild blueberry rooibos and alpine peppermint, there's something for everyone. Visitors can enjoy their teas in loose leaf or sachet form, or opt for the adorable 'Tea House' box featuring 15 curated tea bags.
placeMetadata.address: 211A Bear St, Banff, AB T1L 1C9, Canada

placeMetadata.name: University of Alberta Botanic Garden
placeMetadata.description: 240-acre park with a wide variety of trees, plants & flowers, indoor showhouses & themed gardens.
placeMetadata.generatedDescription: The University of Alberta Botanic Garden is a sprawling 240-acre natural oasis located just outside Edmonton. It boasts an impressive array of plants from around the globe, themed gardens, and serene water features. The highlight is the traditional Japanese-style Kurimoto Garden with its winding pathways, tranquil ponds, and lush greenery. Families can enjoy the children's map with attractions like a castle and hedge maze.
placeMetadata.address: 51227 AB-60, Parkland County, AB T7Y 1C5, Canada

placeMetadata.name: Royal Alberta Museum
placeMetadata.description: Exhibits on Alberta's geological & human history, including First Peoples, plus fossils & wildlife.
placeMetadata.generatedDescription: The Royal Alberta Museum, located in downtown Edmonton's Arts District, is the largest museum in Western Canada. With over 82,000 square feet of exhibition space, it houses a diverse collection of artifacts that offer insight into Alberta's geological and human history. Visitors can explore exhibits on First Peoples, fossils, wildlife, and the province's landscape from petroglyphs to prehistoric dinosaurs. The museum also delves into the survival of First Nations in harsh lands and how Alberta has evolved since then.
placeMetadata.address: 9810 103a Ave NW, Edmonton, AB T5J 0G2, Canada

placeMetadata.name: St. Albert Botanic Park
placeMetadata.generatedDescription: Immerse yourself in the beauty of nature at St. Albert Botanic Park, a charming five-acre botanical garden located in St. Albert. This picturesque park showcases an array of meticulously cultivated trees, shrubs, perennials, and vegetables across themed gardens such as flowering trees, evergreens, xeriscape, shade, and cottage-style perennials.
placeMetadata.address: 265 Sturgeon Rd, St. Albert, AB T8N 3S9, Canada

placeMetadata.name: Town of Banff
placeMetadata.description: Town Hall building home to the Banff townsite government headquarters, within Banff National Park.
placeMetadata.generatedDescription: Nestled within Banff National Park, the Town of Banff is a bustling hub offering a mix of urban amenities and natural beauty. Visitors can explore the downtown area, which boasts an array of attractions such as shops, eateries, art galleries, and museums like the Banff Park Museum and Whyte Museum of the Canadian Rockies. For those seeking to tie the knot amidst stunning landscapes, special permits from both the National Park and Town Hall are required.
placeMetadata.address: 110 Bear St, Banff, AB T1L 1H7, Canada

placeMetadata.name: Sandman Signature Edmonton South Hotel
placeMetadata.description: Bright quarters with free Wi-Fi in a low-key hotel with an indoor pool, 2 restaurants & a gym.
placeMetadata.generatedDescription: The Sandman Signature Edmonton South Hotel in Edmonton, Alberta offers bright and comfortable quarters with free Wi-Fi, flat-screen cable TV, and coffee facilities. The hotel features an indoor pool, gym, and two restaurants. Guests have praised the friendly and accommodating front desk service as well as the convenient location near the University of Alberta. Additionally, visitors traveling with pets appreciate the pet-friendly accommodations on the ground floor.
placeMetadata.address: 10111 Ellerslie Rd SW, Edmonton, AB T6X 0J3, Canada

placeMetadata.name: Johnston Canyon
placeMetadata.description: National park with hiking trails & bridges to waterfalls, ridges & blue 'ink pot' spring pools.
placeMetadata.generatedDescription: Johnston Canyon is a popular day hiking trail in Banff National Park, known for its stunning blue waterfalls and unique pathways that cling to the cliffside. The hike is accessible year-round, offering different experiences depending on the season. Visitors can explore the Lower Johnston Falls, which covers 1.1 km of fairly flat ground. The canyon features limestone cliffs, cascading waterfalls, and cliffside catwalks along Johnston Creek.
placeMetadata.address: Bow Valley Pkwy, Improvement District No. 9, AB T1L 1K2, Canada

placeMetadata.name: Yamnuska Wolfdog Sanctuary
placeMetadata.description: Wolfdog haven offering guided walks, interactive tours with up-close encounters & a gift shop.
placeMetadata.generatedDescription: Nestled in the heart of Alberta, Yamnuska Wolfdog Sanctuary is a remarkable non-profit haven dedicated to the rehabilitation and care of wolfdogs from across North America. This sanctuary not only provides a safe home for these unique animals but also serves as an educational hub where visitors can learn about their fascinating lives and the challenges they face. With three distinct tour options—Sanctuary Walk, Intro Tour, and Interactive Tour—guests have the opportunity to engage with these captivating creatures up close.
placeMetadata.address: 263156 Range Rd 53, Cochrane, AB T4C1B3, Canada

placeMetadata.name: Best Western Plus South Edmonton Inn & Suites
placeMetadata.description: Understated budget hotel offering free parking & hot breakfast, plus an indoor pool & a waterslide.
placeMetadata.address: 1204 101 St SW, Edmonton, AB T6X 0P1, Canada

placeMetadata.name: Edmonton Valley Zoo
placeMetadata.description: Home to more than 350 animals & focused on conservation, this venerable zoo offers rides & programs.
placeMetadata.generatedDescription: The Edmonton Valley Zoo is a vital part of the city's dedication to wildlife conservation, housing over 350 animals and actively participating in various global conservation initiatives. The zoo showcases a diverse range of species, including local Canadian wildlife and exotic creatures such as snow leopards, Arctic wolves, lemurs, and red pandas. Visitors can engage in educational programs while enjoying outdoor exhibits during the summer months. It's an ideal destination for families looking to spend quality time learning about animals and supporting conservation efforts.
placeMetadata.address: 13315 Buena Vista Rd NW, Edmonton, AB T5J 2R7, Canada

placeMetadata.name: Edmonton International Airport
placeMetadata.generatedDescription: Nestled about an hour from the vibrant city of Edmonton, Edmonton International Airport offers a refreshing travel experience that stands out for its tranquility and efficiency. Unlike larger airports like Vancouver International or Toronto Pearson, this airport boasts shorter security lines—typically under 20 minutes—allowing travelers to breeze through with ease. While it may have an older charm compared to its busier counterparts, it is equipped with all essential facilities.
placeMetadata.address: 1000 Airport Rd, Edmonton International Airport, AB T9E 0V3, Canada

placeMetadata.name: Horse Hill Berry Farm
placeMetadata.generatedDescription: Last summer, I rediscovered the joy of berry picking at Horse Hill Berry Farm, and it was an absolute delight! Nestled just a short drive from the city, this charming farm spans 10 acres filled with luscious raspberries. The season runs from mid-July to mid-August, making it perfect for a sunny afternoon adventure. With no appointment needed and friendly staff ready to assist you, it's easy to dive into the fun of picking your own fruit.
placeMetadata.address: 3203 211 Ave NE, Edmonton, AB T5Y 6P1, Canada

placeMetadata.name: Fort Edmonton Park
placeMetadata.description: Heritage park with recreated architecture from 1885, 1905 & 1920 Edmonton, plus a fort & streetcars.
placeMetadata.generatedDescription: Fort Edmonton Park is a 58-acre living history museum located in the North Saskatchewan River Valley, offering a journey through different eras of Edmonton's history. The park features four sections representing distinct periods: the fur trading era, settlement era, municipal era, and metropolitan era. Visitors can explore replica buildings, interact with costumed performers, enjoy pioneer games and activities like horse-drawn carriages and wagon rides. A fully functional 1919 steam train adds to the immersive experience.
placeMetadata.address: 7000 143 St NW, Edmonton, AB T6H 4P3, Canada

placeMetadata.name: Peyto Lake Viewpoint
placeMetadata.generatedDescription: Nestled just off the Icefields Parkway, about a half-hour north of Lake Louise, Peyto Lake Upper Viewpoint is a gem that showcases the stunning beauty of the Canadian Rockies without requiring extensive hiking skills. This accessible trail features a paved path that makes it stroller- and wheelchair-friendly, allowing visitors of all ages to enjoy its breathtaking views. The short hike to the viewpoint spans 2.6 km with minimal elevation gain, making it an easy trek for families and casual walkers alike.
placeMetadata.address: Lake Louise, AB T0L 1E0, Canada

placeMetadata.name: Toronto Pearson International Airport
placeMetadata.description: Toronto-area airport featuring lots of eateries & shops, free WiFi & rotating art displays.
placeMetadata.generatedDescription: Toronto Pearson International Airport is a well-organized airport with amenities catering to travelers' needs. It offers a wide range of eateries and shops, free WiFi, and rotating art displays for passengers to enjoy. The airport also provides accommodations nearby, such as the Hilton Toronto Airport Hotel & Suites, conveniently located just minutes away. Additionally, Budget Car Rental services are available at the airport for convenient transportation options.
placeMetadata.address: 6301 Silver Dart Dr, Mississauga, ON L5P 1B2, Canada

placeMetadata.name: Banff National Park
placeMetadata.description: Rocky Mountain park offering year-round activities & glacial lakes such as Lake Louise, also a town.
placeMetadata.generatedDescription: Banff National Park, located in western Alberta, is a 2,564-square-mile Rocky Mountain park known for its stunning natural beauty. It was Canada's first national park and remains the most famous and beloved. The park features glacial lakes such as Lake Louise and offers opportunities for breathtaking photography. Visitors can also spot diverse wildlife including bighorn sheep, elk, deer, and possibly moose.
placeMetadata.address: Improvement District No. 9, AB T0L, Canada

placeMetadata.name: Banff Gondola
placeMetadata.description: Calm gondola ride to a mountaintop for sweeping views of surrounding peaks, plus dining & a museum.
placeMetadata.generatedDescription: The Banff Gondola offers a serene ride to the top of Sulphur Mountain, providing breathtaking panoramic views of the surrounding peaks. At the summit, visitors can stroll out to a grassy bluff overlooking Banff town and marvel at the majestic mountains. The gondola ascends in just eight minutes, leading to observation decks and boardwalks at the peak. Additionally, guests can enjoy dining at Sky Bistro, an upscale restaurant with stunning mountain vistas.
placeMetadata.address: 100 Mountain Ave, Banff, AB T1L 1J3, Canada

placeMetadata.name: Hampton Inn by Hilton Edmonton/South, Alberta, Canada
placeMetadata.description: Understated hotel offering complimentary breakfast & Wi-Fi, plus a gym & an indoor pool.
placeMetadata.address: 10020 12 Ave SW, Edmonton, AB T6X 0P9, Canada

placeMetadata.name: Old Strathcona Farmers' Market
placeMetadata.description: Classic brick warehouse open on Saturdays featuring 130+ vendors selling produce, crafts & more.
placeMetadata.generatedDescription: The Old Strathcona Farmers' Market is a classic brick warehouse open on Saturdays, featuring over 130 vendors selling a variety of goods including produce, crafts, and more. It's not just about shopping; visitors can enjoy free entertainment such as street performers and live musicians. The market moves indoors during colder months, ensuring year-round enjoyment. Located in the historic Old Strathcona area, it offers a unique atmosphere with independent shops, restaurants, and bars to explore.
placeMetadata.address: 10310 83 Ave NW, Edmonton, AB T6E 5C3, Canada

placeMetadata.name: Cave and Basin National Historic Site
placeMetadata.description: Canada's first national park, with hot mineral springs in a cave & an outdoor, emerald-colored pool.
placeMetadata.generatedDescription: Cave and Basin National Historic Site is a significant landmark in Canada, as it was the birthplace of the country's national parks system. Discovered by railway workers in 1883, this site offers interactive exhibits that showcase Canada's network of protected places. Visitors can take guided tours of the original cave to learn about its history and culture, including lantern tours for an after-dark experience.
placeMetadata.address: 311 Cave Ave, Banff, AB T1L 1K2, Canada

placeMetadata.name: Elk Island National Park
placeMetadata.description: Large, forested park featuring a refuge for bison, elk & many birds, plus campsites & picnic spots.
placeMetadata.generatedDescription: Elk Island National Park, located just a 30-minute drive east of Edmonton, is a large forested park known for its conservation efforts and diverse wildlife. This UNESCO-designated Biosphere Reserve is home to a dwindling population of Canadian bison, making it one of the best places to encounter these majestic animals in their natural habitat. The park also serves as a refuge for elk and over 250 bird species.
placeMetadata.address: Improvement District No. 13, AB, Canada
